PURPOSE
  NZBGet PP script to maintain files in a flat directory structure.

STATUS
  Working as of: 2019-02-10

DETAILS
  This post-processing script looks for files based on a list
  of approved extensions then moves them to a defined folder.
  It can optionally also remove the original download directory
  and any remaining files in it. Tested on Debian with NZBGet 20.0.

INSTALL
  01 : Copy the file to your NZBGet scripts folder and chmod +x.
  02 : Set config options via the NZBGet settings menu.
  03 : Use and enjoy.

